The paper deals with the problem of beamforming for wireless broadcasting systems with simultaneous information and power transmission, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also considers the problem under imperfect channel state information, which is a common issue in control systems (cs.SY). The use of semidefinite programming techniques is a common optimization tool in machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.MM), which are also relevant to the paper.
